2.body: Setting up owoTrack shouldn't be too difficult. If you are using Android, owoTrack should automatically detect and connect to SlimeVR server. If you are using iOS, connecting owoTrack to SlimeVR server will be a little more difficult, as you will need to manually enter the ip address of the device running SlimeVR server. It is suggested to read the Android and iOS connection guides for more info.
2.title: Setup

3.body: Some phones have better IMUs (Inertial Measurement Unit) than others. This can lead to some phones having better tracking quality than others, however it does depend on how the manufacturer has configered the phone. The IMU models used by many phones are documented on this site, but a better IMU doesn't always mean better tracking.
3.title: Specs of phones

4.body: Warning Please do not buy phones for Full Body Tracking. They will be more expensive than buying SlimeVR Trackers, and offer worse tracking. It is reccomended to buy or build actual SlimeVR Trackers instead. Warning owoTrack is mostly a proof of concept. Using phones for trackers does not lead to the best results, and fixing bad tracking quality is not always possible. Danger Strapping phones (or tablets) to your body can damage or break the devices, which can lead to you getting covered in broken glass. Take caution when strapping devices to you!
4.title: Important notes

5.body: moveTrackVR utilizes uncalibrated sensor data instead of the (Game) Rotation Vector. This approach bypasses any automated calibration algorithms implemented by the phone. Many phones incorporate customized sensor algorithms, including drift correction and custom dead zones, which vary across different devices. Unfortunately, the (Game) Rotation Vector on most phones tends to be unreliable due to these customized algorithms. moveTrackVR is compatible with SlimeVR. moveTrackVR is less known, but is the 2nd option if owoTrack doesn't find your sensors. moveTrackVR is only available for Android, and can be downloaded from the Github
5.title: MoveTrackVR

7.title: Android Devices

8.body: Make sure you have installed owoTrack on your android device Open the owoTrack app. Make sure that the rotation sensor is checked. Make sure the phone is on the same network as the PC running SlimeVR server. Click the auto-connect button on the phone. If the phone fails to connect, check the step above, and try again.
8.breadcrumbs: Android Devices » Connecting to SlimeVR » Connecting to SlimeVR
8.title: Connecting to SlimeVR

9.body: If autoconnect fails, you can manually enter the local IP of your computer as shown below. To find the IP address of a windows computer, open cmd by typing in the search bar, then type ‘ipconfig’. Look for the network adapter that you are using, and take note of the IPv4 Address. This will usually be something like 192.168.x.x. This may differ based on your network setup. Enter the IP address that you found into the first input box, then click connect. You should now be connected. You can now use your phone as you would any other slimevr tracker and configure it on the server. Info The phone may disconnect if it doesn't allow running apps in the background. To fix this, you can visit https://dontkillmyapp.com/ to find a fix for your phone.
